button._low.comment: Text in button, which represents the 'low' picture quality
button._medium.comment: Text in button, which represents the 'medium' picture quality
button._high.comment: Text in button, which represents the 'high' picture quality
button._buyMore.comment: Text in button, which allows user to buy more credits
button._uploadReferences.comment: Text in button, which allows user to upload references
button._success.comment: Text in button, which indicates that the operation was successful
button._generating.comment: Text in button, which indicates that the operation is in progress
button._failed.comment: Text in button, which indicates that the operation failed
button._download.comment: Text in button, which allows user to download the result
button._fast.comment: Text in button, which allows user to set the 'fast speed' mode to fast to generate the image, must translate to 'Fast speed'
button._relax.comment: Text in button, which allows user to set the 'slow speed' mode to relax to generate the image, must translate to 'Slow speed'
button._turbo.comment: Text in button, which allows user to set the 'extreme speed' mode to turbo to generate the image, must translate to 'Extreme speed'
button._more.comment: Text in button, which allows user to see more options
button._generate.comment: Text in button, which allows user to generate the image
button._history.comment: Text in button, which allows user to see the history of generated images
button._generateNew.comment: Text in button, which allows user to draw a new picture

field._finalPrompt.comment: Final Drawing prompt used to generate the image
field._elements.comment: Drawing style used to generate the image
field._traceId.comment: Trace ID for tracing the request of generating the image, do not translate it, keep it as 'Trace ID'

description.aspect: --aspect, Changes the aspect ratio of the generated image, default value depends on the model and mode
description.chaos: --chaos, Adjusts the degree of variation in the generated image, the higher the number, the more unique and unexpected the generated image, range is 0-100, default is 1
description.fast: Ignores current settings and runs a single generation task in 'fast speed' mode, no default value
description.iw: --iw, Sets the importance of image prompts relative to text prompts during the generation process, range is 0-2, default is 1
description.no: --no, Indicates the generation system to attempt to exclude certain elements, for example `--no plants` will attempt to generate images without plants, no default value
description._no.comment: Description of the no parameter, translate it as 'Exclude'
description.quality: --quality, Sets the quality and rendering time of the generated image, range is .25, .5, or 1, default is 1
description.random: Adds a random base style code to the prompt, can use `--style random-16`, `--style random-64`, or `--style random-128` to get random style effects of different lengths, no default value
description.relax: Overrides current settings to run a single task in 'slow speed' mode, no default value
description.repeat: --repeat, Creates multiple tasks from one prompt, range is 1-40, default is 1
description.seed: --seed, Starting visual noise for generated images, range is 0-4294967295, default is randomly generated
description.stop: --stop, Stops the task at any stage of the generation process, range is 10-100, default is 100 (i.e., fully generated)
description.style: --style, switches between different versions or styles of Midjourney or Niji models, for example raw, cute, expressive, original, scenic, default value depends on the model and mode
description.stylize: --stylize, adjusts the intensity of the default aesthetic style of Midjourney applied in generation tasks, range is 0-1000, default is 100
description.tile: --tile, Generates an image that can be used for seamless tiling to create seamless patterns, no default value
description.turbo: Overrides current settings to run a single task in 'extreme speed' mode, no default value
description.weird: --weird, explores uncommon aesthetic styles with experimental nature, range is 0-3000, default is 0
description.translation: Enables automatic translation during generation, non-Chinese content will be automatically translated to English input for Midjourney
description.imageWeight: --iw, adjusts the weight of image prompts relative to text prompts, range is 0-2, default is 1
description.niji: --niji, When enabled, generated images will use the Niji model, producing anime-style images
description.uploadReferences: Upload images as references for generation, supports up to 5 images. If more than 1 image is uploaded, they will be automatically merged
description.raw: --raw, When enabled, generated images will use the Midjourney model, producing original style images
description.prompt: Enter commands, if additional parameters are added, they will override default preset parameters, e.g., adding `--stylize 200` will force the final command to use `--stylize 200`

action.generate: Click this button to start generating images
action.variation1: Adjust variation of the first image
action.variation2: Adjust variation of the second image
action.variation3: Adjust variation of the third image
action.variation4: Adjust variation of the fourth image

message.promptPlaceholder: Please enter a sentence to describe the image you want to generate, for example: a cute cat. Additional parameters will override default preset parameters
message._promptPlaceholder.comment: Placeholder text in the prompt field
message.uploadReferencesExceed: You can upload up to 5 images at most
message._uploadReferencesExceed.comment: Error message when the number of uploaded images exceeds the limit
message._uploadReferencesSuccess.comment: Success message when images are uploaded successfully
message.uploadReferencesError: Failed to upload images, please try again later
message._uploadReferencesError.comment: Error message when images fail to upload
message._startTaskSuccess.comment: Success message when the drawing task is started successfully
message._startTaskFailed.comment: Error message when the drawing task fails to start
message._generating.comment: Message when the image is being generated
message._noOperations.comment: Message when there are no available operations
message.noTasks: No historical tasks, please start a new task first
message._noTasks.comment: Message when there are no historical tasks

model._general.comment: The name of a model which used for general image generation
model._niji.comment: The name of a model which used for anime-style image generation, do not translate, keep it as 'Niji'

name._model.comment: The model name, model is a term in machine learning, which is used to generate images
name._aspect.comment: The name of the aspect parameter
name._ratio.comment: The name of the ratio parameter
name._chaos.comment: The name of the chaos parameter, translate is as 'rate of messy'
name._fast.comment: The name of the fast mode, which is used to generate images quickly, translate it as 'Fast speed'
name._nijiStyle.comment: The name of the nijiStyle parameter, do not translate it, keep it as 'Niji'
name._version.comment: The name of the version parameter
name._imageWeight.comment: The name of the imageWeight parameter
name._no.comment: The name of the no parameter, which is used to exclude certain elements, translate it as 'Exclude'
name._quality.comment: The name of the quality parameter, which is used to set the quality of the generated image
name._random.comment: The name of the random parameter, which is used to add random style effects
name._relax.comment: The name of the relax mode, which is used to generate images in 'slow speed' mode, translate it as 'slow speed'
name._repeat.comment: The name of the repeat parameter, which is used to create multiple tasks from one prompt
name._seed.comment: The name of the seed parameter, which is used to set the starting visual noise
name._stop.comment: The name of the stop parameter, which is used to stop the task at any stage
name._style.comment: The name of the style parameter, which is used to switch between different versions or styles of models
name._stylize.comment: The name of the stylize parameter, which is used to adjust the intensity of the default aesthetic style
name._tile.comment: The name of the tile parameter, which is used to generate images that can be used for seamless tiling
name._turbo.comment: The name of the turbo mode, which is used to generate images in the 'Extreme speed' mode, translate it as 'Extreme speed'
name._weird.comment: The name of the weird parameter, which is used to explore uncommon aesthetic styles, translate it as 'Weirdness'
name._translation.comment: The name of the translation parameter, which is used to enable automatic translation during generation
name._advanced.comment: The name of the advanced mode, which is used to enable advanced mode
name._niji.comment: The name of the niji parameter, which is used to enable the Niji model, do not translate it, keep it as 'Niji'
name._ignore.comment: The name of the ignore parameter, which is used to ignore certain elements
name._prompt.comment: The name of the prompt parameter, which is used to enter drawing instructions
name._raw.comment: The name of the raw parameter, which is used to enable the Midjourney model
